-- =====================================================================
-- Auto-generated seed data for local development
-- Generated at 2025-09-16T00:59:50.850Z
--
-- PURPOSE
--   Provides 1000 localized (PH) mock users with professionals, education,
--   work history, skills, and a single link each for feature prototyping
--   (search, filtering, UI iteration).
--
-- USAGE (DESTRUCTIVE)
--   1. supabase db reset        # WARNING: wipes local dev DB
--   2. psql $SUPABASE_DB_URL -f supabase/seed.sql
--      OR docker exec -i supabase-db psql -U postgres -d postgres < supabase/seed.sql
--
-- REGENERATION
--   From repo root (app dir contains script):
--     cd app && npm run seed:generate
--   Deterministic output via faker.seed(42). Change seed for a new dataset.
--
-- AUTH / PASSWORD
--   All users share the bcrypt hash for password: 'password'. Replace HASH if needed.
--   Direct inserts into auth.users assume local dev environment with relaxed policies.
--
-- PERFORMANCE OPT
--   Triggers that maintain professionals.value_profile are disabled during bulk load
--   and a single batch rebuild call per professional is executed, then triggers re-enabled.
--
-- DATA MODEL NOTES
--   * value_profile is a concatenated denormalized summary (education/work/skills/links)
--   * Tags include sector, town, province, and experience category (fresh/mid/senior)
--   * Some fresh users may have 0 work history entries (intentional)
--
-- UNIQUENESS STRATEGY
--   Emails: first.last(+n) to avoid collisions. first occurrence has no suffix.
--   Names: best-effort uniqueness of (first_name,last_name). On repeated collision a compound first name is generated (e.g., "Ana Maria").
--   Phones: sequential unique starting at +639000000000.
--
-- FUTURE EXTENSIONS (commented in script)
--   * Address columns (street_address, barangay, town, province, postal_code)
--   * Additional links per professional
--   * Locality-based additional tags (barangay)
--
-- LIMITATIONS
--   * Not production-grade anonymization—fabricated data only.
--   * Email domain fixed (@example.test).
--   * Single link per user to keep dataset lean.
--   * Phones not validated against real PH telco numbering blocks.
--
-- DISTRIBUTION
--   400 fresh (0-1y) / 350 mid (2-5y) / 250 senior (6-25y)
-- =====================================================================
